newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysia Oct crude palm oil output up 2.18 pct.
newsitem.headline: Malaysia Oct crude palm oil output up 2.18 pct.

text.p: Malaysia's crude palm oil output rose 2.18 percent to 883,579 tonnes in October from 864,730 in September and against 768,440 tonnes in October 1995, the Palm Oil Registration and Licensing Authority (PORLA) said on Friday.
October palm oil exports were 727,629 tonnes against 649,688 in September and 615,089 in October last year, it said.
PORLA said Peninsular Malaysia's crude palm oil output rose 0.85 percent to 651,951 tonnes in October from 646,448 in September and 521,227 tonnes in October 1995.
Output from east Malaysian states of Sabah and Sarawak rose 6.11 percent to 231,628 tonnes in October from 218,282 tonnes in September and against 174,603 tonnes in October 1995.
Malaysia's palm kernel oil production rose 7.12 percent to 107,646 tonnes in October from 100,490 in September and against 99,023 tonnes in October last year.
